+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AVjtJZEfSCej1WQy7i7bZN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015jx9XMS3EZDLAPsrgzCGY5","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-analytics-dashboard.md","content":"# Analytics Dashboard Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a multi-tenant analytics dashboard HTTP API in TypeScript with user management, event ingestion, query engine, dashboard CRUD, and data export.\n\n**Architecture:** Express.js REST API backed by SQLite (via better-sqlite3). Each request that touches tenant data goes through a JWT auth middleware that injects the tenant context. All five feature areas are organized as Express routers, assembled in `src/app.ts` which exports `createApp`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ES2022, Node16), Express 4, better-sqlite3, jsonwebtoken, uuid, Vitest for tests.\n\n---\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\nsrc/\n  app.ts          # createApp() – wires db, routers, exports Express app\n  db.ts           # Opens/migrates SQLite DB from schema.sql\n  auth.ts         # JWT helpers: sign, verify, authMiddleware\n  routes/\n    users.ts      # POST /register, POST /login, GET /me, PATCH /users/:id/role\n    events.ts     # POST /events, POST /events/batch\n    query.ts      # POST /query  (count | timeseries | breakdown)\n    dashboards.ts # CRUD /dashboards, /dashboards/:id\n    export.ts     # GET /export/events, GET /export/dashboards/:id\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Database Layer\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/db.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function openDb(dbPath = ':memory:'): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = fs.readFileSync(\n    path.resolve(__dirname, '../schema.sql'),\n    'utf8'\n  );\n  db.exec(schema);\n  return db;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build to verify TypeScript compiles**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\nExpected: no errors (or only \"no input files\" since app.ts doesn't exist yet — that's fine once we write it).\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Auth Helpers\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/auth.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/auth.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';\nimport { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\n\nconst JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET ?? 'dev-secret-change-me';\n\nexport interface JwtPayload {\n  userId: string;\n  tenantId: string;\n  role: string;\n}\n\nexport function signToken(payload: JwtPayload): string {\n  return jwt.sign(payload, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '7d' });\n}\n\nexport function verifyToken(token: string): JwtPayload {\n  return jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET) as JwtPayload;\n}\n\n// Extends Express Request with auth context\ndeclare global {\n  namespace Express {\n    interface Request {\n      auth?: JwtPayload;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport function authMiddleware(req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void {\n  const header = req.headers.authorization;\n  if (!header?.startsWith('Bearer ')) {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n    return;\n  }\n  try {\n    req.auth = verifyToken(header.slice(7));\n    next();\n  } catch {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid token' });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Users Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/users.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/users.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport crypto from 'crypto';\nimport { signToken, authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\nfunction hashPassword(password: string): string {\n  return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(password).digest('hex');\n}\n\nexport function createUsersRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // POST /auth/register\n  router.post('/auth/register', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const { email, password, tenantId } = req.body as {\n      email?: string;\n      password?: string;\n      tenantId?: string;\n    };\n    if (!email || !password || !tenantId) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'email, password, tenantId required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = uuidv4();\n    const password_hash = hashPassword(password);\n    try {\n      db.prepare(\n        'INSERT INTO users (id, email, password_hash, tenant_id, role) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n      ).run(id, email, password_hash, tenantId, 'viewer');\n      const token = signToken({ userId: id, tenantId, role: 'viewer' });\n      res.status(201).json({ token, userId: id, tenantId, role: 'viewer' });\n    } catch {\n      res.status(409).json({ error: 'Email already registered' });\n    }\n  });\n\n  // POST /auth/login\n  router.post('/auth/login', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const { email, password } = req.body as { email?: string; password?: string };\n    if (!email || !password) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'email and password required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const user = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?').get(email) as\n      | { id: string; tenant_id: string; role: string; password_hash: string }\n      | undefined;\n    if (!user || user.password_hash !== hashPassword(password)) {\n      res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const token = signToken({ userId: user.id, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role });\n    res.json({ token, userId: user.id, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role });\n  });\n\n  // GET /me\n  router.get('/me', authMiddleware, (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const user = db\n      .prepare('SELECT id, email, tenant_id, role, created_at FROM users WHERE id = ?')\n      .get(auth.userId);\n    if (!user) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json(user);\n  });\n\n  // PATCH /users/:id/role  (admin only, same tenant)\n  router.patch('/users/:id/role', authMiddleware, (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    if (auth.role !== 'admin') {\n      res.status(403).json({ error: 'Admin only' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const { role } = req.body as { role?: string };\n    const validRoles = ['admin', 'editor', 'viewer'];\n    if (!role || !validRoles.includes(role)) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'role must be admin, editor, or viewer' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const result = db\n      .prepare('UPDATE users SET role = ? WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .run(role, req.params.id, auth.tenantId);\n    if (result.changes === 0) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found in your tenant' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json({ updated: true });\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Events Router (Ingestion)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/events.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/events.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\ninterface EventInput {\n  name?: string;\n  properties?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  timestamp?: string;\n}\n\nexport function createEventsRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // All event routes require auth\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  // POST /events  – single event\n  router.post('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { name, properties = {}, timestamp = new Date().toISOString() } =\n      req.body as EventInput;\n    if (!name) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'name is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = uuidv4();\n    db.prepare(\n      'INSERT INTO events (id, tenant_id, name, properties, timestamp) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n    ).run(id, auth.tenantId, name, JSON.stringify(properties), timestamp);\n    res.status(201).json({ id });\n  });\n\n  // POST /events/batch\n  router.post('/batch', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { events } = req.body as { events?: EventInput[] };\n    if (!Array.isArray(events) || events.length === 0) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'events array required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const insert = db.prepare(\n      'INSERT INTO events (id, tenant_id, name, properties, timestamp) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n    );\n    const insertMany = db.transaction((evts: EventInput[]) => {\n      const ids: string[] = [];\n      for (const evt of evts) {\n        if (!evt.name) continue;\n        const id = uuidv4();\n        insert.run(\n          id,\n          auth.tenantId,\n          evt.name,\n          JSON.stringify(evt.properties ?? {}),\n          evt.timestamp ?? new Date().toISOString()\n        );\n        ids.push(id);\n      }\n      return ids;\n    });\n    const ids = insertMany(events);\n    res.status(201).json({ inserted: ids.length, ids });\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Query Engine Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/query.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/query.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\ninterface QueryBody {\n  type: 'count' | 'timeseries' | 'breakdown';\n  eventName?: string;\n  filters?: Record<string, string>;\n  // timeseries options\n  startDate?: string;\n  endDate?: string;\n  interval?: 'day' | 'hour' | 'week';\n  // breakdown options\n  breakdownProperty?: string;\n}\n\nexport function createQueryRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  router.post('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const body = req.body as QueryBody;\n\n    if (!body.type) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'type is required (count|timeseries|breakdown)' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      switch (body.type) {\n        case 'count': {\n          let sql = 'SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ?';\n          const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n          if (body.eventName) {\n            sql += ' AND name = ?';\n            params.push(body.eventName);\n          }\n          const row = db.prepare(sql).get(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]])) as {\n            count: number;\n          };\n          res.json({ count: row.count });\n          break;\n        }\n\n        case 'timeseries': {\n          const intervalFormat =\n            body.interval === 'hour'\n              ? '%Y-%m-%dT%H:00'\n              : body.interval === 'week'\n              ? '%Y-W%W'\n              : '%Y-%m-%d';\n          let sql = `\n            SELECT strftime('${intervalFormat}', timestamp) as bucket, COUNT(*) as count\n            FROM events\n            WHERE tenant_id = ?\n          `;\n          const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n          if (body.eventName) {\n            sql += ' AND name = ?';\n            params.push(body.eventName);\n          }\n          if (body.startDate) {\n            sql += ' AND timestamp >= ?';\n            params.push(body.startDate);\n          }\n          if (body.endDate) {\n            sql += ' AND timestamp <= ?';\n            params.push(body.endDate);\n          }\n          sql += ` GROUP BY bucket ORDER BY bucket`;\n          const rows = db.prepare(sql).all(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]));\n          res.json({ series: rows });\n          break;\n        }\n\n        case 'breakdown': {\n          if (!body.breakdownProperty) {\n            res.status(400).json({ error: 'breakdownProperty required for breakdown query' });\n            return;\n          }\n          const prop = body.breakdownProperty;\n          let sql = `\n            SELECT json_extract(properties, '$.\"${prop}\"') as value, COUNT(*) as count\n            FROM events\n            WHERE tenant_id = ?\n          `;\n          const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n          if (body.eventName) {\n            sql += ' AND name = ?';\n            params.push(body.eventName);\n          }\n          sql += ' GROUP BY value ORDER BY count DESC';\n          const rows = db.prepare(sql).all(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]));\n          res.json({ breakdown: rows });\n          break;\n        }\n\n        default:\n          res.status(400).json({ error: 'Unknown query type' });\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      res.status(500).json({ error: String(err) });\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Dashboards Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/dashboards.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/dashboards.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\ninterface DashboardRow {\n  id: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  name: string;\n  owner_id: string;\n  config: string;\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport function createDashboardsRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  // GET /dashboards\n  router.get('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const rows = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE tenant_id = ? ORDER BY created_at DESC')\n      .all(auth.tenantId) as DashboardRow[];\n    res.json(\n      rows.map((r) => ({ ...r, config: JSON.parse(r.config) }))\n    );\n  });\n\n  // POST /dashboards\n  router.post('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { name, config = {} } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: object };\n    if (!name) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'name is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = uuidv4();\n    const now = new Date().toISOString();\n    db.prepare(\n      'INSERT INTO dashboards (id, tenant_id, name, owner_id, config, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n    ).run(id, auth.tenantId, name, auth.userId, JSON.stringify(config), now, now);\n    res.status(201).json({ id, name, tenantId: auth.tenantId });\n  });\n\n  // GET /dashboards/:id\n  router.get('/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const row = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .get(req.params.id, auth.tenantId) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n    if (!row) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json({ ...row, config: JSON.parse(row.config) });\n  });\n\n  // PATCH /dashboards/:id\n  router.patch('/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { name, config } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: object };\n    const existing = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .get(req.params.id, auth.tenantId) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n    if (!existing) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const now = new Date().toISOString();\n    const newName = name ?? existing.name;\n    const newConfig = config !== undefined ? JSON.stringify(config) : existing.config;\n    db.prepare(\n      'UPDATE dashboards SET name = ?, config = ?, updated_at = ? WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?'\n    ).run(newName, newConfig, now, req.params.id, auth.tenantId);\n    res.json({ updated: true });\n  });\n\n  // DELETE /dashboards/:id\n  router.delete('/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const result = db\n      .prepare('DELETE FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .run(req.params.id, auth.tenantId);\n    if (result.changes === 0) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json({ deleted: true });\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Export Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/export.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2, Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/export.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\nfunction rowsToCsv(rows: Record<string, unknown>[]): string {\n  if (rows.length === 0) return '';\n  const headers = Object.keys(rows[0]);\n  const lines = [\n    headers.join(','),\n    ...rows.map((r) =>\n      headers\n        .map((h) => {\n          const val = r[h];\n          const str = val === null || val === undefined ? '' : String(val);\n          // Escape quotes and wrap in quotes if contains comma, quote, or newline\n          if (str.includes(',') || str.includes('\"') || str.includes('\\n')) {\n            return `\"${str.replace(/\"/g, '\"\"')}\"`;\n          }\n          return str;\n        })\n        .join(',')\n    ),\n  ];\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function createExportRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  // GET /export/events?format=json|csv&eventName=...\n  router.get('/events', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n    const eventName = req.query.eventName as string | undefined;\n\n    let sql = 'SELECT * FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ?';\n    const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n    if (eventName) {\n      sql += ' AND name = ?';\n      params.push(eventName);\n    }\n    sql += ' ORDER BY timestamp DESC';\n\n    const rows = db.prepare(sql).all(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]])) as Record<\n      string,\n      unknown\n    >[];\n\n    if (format === 'csv') {\n      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n      res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', 'attachment; filename=\"events.csv\"');\n      res.send(rowsToCsv(rows));\n    } else {\n      res.json(rows);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // GET /export/dashboards/:id?format=json|csv\n  router.get('/dashboards/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n    const dashboard = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .get(req.params.id, auth.tenantId) as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;\n\n    if (!dashboard) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (format === 'csv') {\n      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n      res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', `attachment; filename=\"dashboard-${req.params.id}.csv\"`);\n      res.send(rowsToCsv([dashboard]));\n    } else {\n      res.json({ ...dashboard, config: JSON.parse(dashboard.config as string) });\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: App Entry Point\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1–7\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/app.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { openDb } from './db.js';\nimport { createUsersRouter } from './routes/users.js';\nimport { createEventsRouter } from './routes/events.js';\nimport { createQueryRouter } from './routes/query.js';\nimport { createDashboardsRouter } from './routes/dashboards.js';\nimport { createExportRouter } from './routes/export.js';\n\nexport function createApp(db?: Database.Database): express.Application {\n  const database = db ?? openDb();\n  const app = express();\n\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  // Mount routers\n  app.use('/', createUsersRouter(database));\n  app.use('/events', createEventsRouter(database));\n  app.use('/query', createQueryRouter(database));\n  app.use('/dashboards', createDashboardsRouter(database));\n  app.use('/export', createExportRouter(database));\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Full build**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1\n```\n\nExpected: no errors.\n\n**Step 3: Lint**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run lint 2>&1\n```\n\nExpected: no errors.\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tests/app.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 8\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/tests/app.test.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../app.js';\nimport { openDb } from '../db.js';\n\nfunction makeApp() {\n  const db = openDb(); // fresh in-memory DB each time\n  return createApp(db);\n}\n\ndescribe('User Management', () => {\n  it('registers a new user and returns a token', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const res = await request(app).post('/auth/register').send({\n      email: 'alice@example.com',\n      password: 'secret',\n      tenantId: 'acme',\n    });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(res.body.role).toBe('viewer');\n  });\n\n  it('rejects duplicate email', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'a@b.com', password: 'x', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'a@b.com', password: 'y', tenantId: 't1' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(409);\n  });\n\n  it('logs in with correct credentials', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'b@c.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 't2' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/login')\n      .send({ email: 'b@c.com', password: 'pw' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeTruthy();\n  });\n\n  it('rejects wrong password', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'c@d.com', password: 'correct', tenantId: 't3' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/login')\n      .send({ email: 'c@d.com', password: 'wrong' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('returns profile for /me', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const reg = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'd@e.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 't4' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get('/me')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${reg.body.token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.email).toBe('d@e.com');\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for /me without token', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const res = await request(app).get('/me');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Data Ingestion', () => {\n  it('ingests a single event', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'e@f.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenant1' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/events')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeTruthy();\n  });\n\n  it('ingests a batch of events', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'f@g.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenant2' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({\n        events: [\n          { name: 'click', properties: { button: 'signup' } },\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/about' } },\n        ],\n      });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.inserted).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for unauthenticated event ingestion', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const res = await request(app).post('/events').send({ name: 'test' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Query Engine', () => {\n  async function setupWithEvents() {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token, tenantId } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'q@r.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'queryTenant' });\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({\n        events: [\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' }, timestamp: '2024-01-01T10:00:00Z' },\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/about' }, timestamp: '2024-01-01T11:00:00Z' },\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' }, timestamp: '2024-01-02T10:00:00Z' },\n          { name: 'click', properties: { button: 'cta' }, timestamp: '2024-01-02T12:00:00Z' },\n        ],\n      });\n    return { app, token, tenantId };\n  }\n\n  it('counts all events', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'count' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(4);\n  });\n\n  it('counts events by name', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'count', eventName: 'page_view' });\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(3);\n  });\n\n  it('returns timeseries bucketed by day', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'timeseries', eventName: 'page_view', interval: 'day' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.series.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('returns breakdown by property', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'breakdown', eventName: 'page_view', breakdownProperty: 'url' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.breakdown[0].value).toBe('/home');\n    expect(res.body.breakdown[0].count).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('enforces tenant isolation in queries', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: t1 } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'ta@a.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenantA' });\n    const { body: t2 } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'tb@b.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenantB' });\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/events')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1.token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'secret_event' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t2.token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'count' });\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(0);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Dashboard CRUD', () => {\n  async function setup() {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'dash@test.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'dashTenant' });\n    return { app, token };\n  }\n\n  it('creates and retrieves a dashboard', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const create = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'My Dashboard', config: { widgets: [] } });\n    expect(create.status).toBe(201);\n    const id = create.body.id;\n    const get = await request(app)\n      .get(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(get.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(get.body.name).toBe('My Dashboard');\n  });\n\n  it('updates a dashboard', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const { body: { id } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'Old Name' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .patch(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'New Name' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.updated).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  it('deletes a dashboard', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const { body: { id } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'To Delete' });\n    const del = await request(app)\n      .delete(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(del.status).toBe(200);\n    const get = await request(app)\n      .get(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(get.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Data Export', () => {\n  async function setup() {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'exp@test.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'expTenant' });\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({\n        events: [\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } },\n          { name: 'click', properties: { button: 'cta' } },\n        ],\n      });\n    return { app, token };\n  }\n\n  it('exports events as JSON', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get('/export/events?format=json')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body)).toBe(true);\n    expect(res.body.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('exports events as CSV', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get('/export/events?format=csv')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.headers['content-type']).toMatch(/text\\/csv/);\n    expect(res.text).toContain('page_view');\n  });\n\n  it('exports dashboard as JSON', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const { body: { id } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'Export Me' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get(`/export/dashboards/${id}?format=json`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.name).toBe('Export Me');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm test 2>&1\n```\n\nExpected: all tests pass.\n\n**Step 3: Full lint + build**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run lint && npm run build 2>&1\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Commit\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 9\n\n**Step 1: Commit all source**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: implement multi-tenant analytics dashboard API\"\n```\n\n**Step 2: Review diff**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && git diff HEAD~1 --stat\n```\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":123,"cache_read_input_tokens":26874,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":123},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3dd57936-1483-468c-858b-275385d7c531","uuid":"b470796d-4808-4338-91e6-1337ca564719"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015jx9XMS3EZDLAPsrgzCGY5","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-analytics-dashboard.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3dd57936-1483-468c-858b-275385d7c531","uuid":"90b7ba2e-f8f7-46d8-90f9-4fb53ad4a30a","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-analytics-dashboard.md","content":"# Analytics Dashboard Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a multi-tenant analytics dashboard HTTP API in TypeScript with user management, event ingestion, query engine, dashboard CRUD, and data export.\n\n**Architecture:** Express.js REST API backed by SQLite (via better-sqlite3). Each request that touches tenant data goes through a JWT auth middleware that injects the tenant context. All five feature areas are organized as Express routers, assembled in `src/app.ts` which exports `createApp`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ES2022, Node16), Express 4, better-sqlite3, jsonwebtoken, uuid, Vitest for tests.\n\n---\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\nsrc/\n  app.ts          # createApp() – wires db, routers, exports Express app\n  db.ts           # Opens/migrates SQLite DB from schema.sql\n  auth.ts         # JWT helpers: sign, verify, authMiddleware\n  routes/\n    users.ts      # POST /register, POST /login, GET /me, PATCH /users/:id/role\n    events.ts     # POST /events, POST /events/batch\n    query.ts      # POST /query  (count | timeseries | breakdown)\n    dashboards.ts # CRUD /dashboards, /dashboards/:id\n    export.ts     # GET /export/events, GET /export/dashboards/:id\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Database Layer\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/db.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function openDb(dbPath = ':memory:'): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = fs.readFileSync(\n    path.resolve(__dirname, '../schema.sql'),\n    'utf8'\n  );\n  db.exec(schema);\n  return db;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build to verify TypeScript compiles**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\nExpected: no errors (or only \"no input files\" since app.ts doesn't exist yet — that's fine once we write it).\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Auth Helpers\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/auth.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/auth.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';\nimport { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\n\nconst JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET ?? 'dev-secret-change-me';\n\nexport interface JwtPayload {\n  userId: string;\n  tenantId: string;\n  role: string;\n}\n\nexport function signToken(payload: JwtPayload): string {\n  return jwt.sign(payload, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '7d' });\n}\n\nexport function verifyToken(token: string): JwtPayload {\n  return jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET) as JwtPayload;\n}\n\n// Extends Express Request with auth context\ndeclare global {\n  namespace Express {\n    interface Request {\n      auth?: JwtPayload;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport function authMiddleware(req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void {\n  const header = req.headers.authorization;\n  if (!header?.startsWith('Bearer ')) {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });\n    return;\n  }\n  try {\n    req.auth = verifyToken(header.slice(7));\n    next();\n  } catch {\n    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid token' });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Users Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/users.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/users.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport crypto from 'crypto';\nimport { signToken, authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\nfunction hashPassword(password: string): string {\n  return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(password).digest('hex');\n}\n\nexport function createUsersRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // POST /auth/register\n  router.post('/auth/register', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const { email, password, tenantId } = req.body as {\n      email?: string;\n      password?: string;\n      tenantId?: string;\n    };\n    if (!email || !password || !tenantId) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'email, password, tenantId required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = uuidv4();\n    const password_hash = hashPassword(password);\n    try {\n      db.prepare(\n        'INSERT INTO users (id, email, password_hash, tenant_id, role) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n      ).run(id, email, password_hash, tenantId, 'viewer');\n      const token = signToken({ userId: id, tenantId, role: 'viewer' });\n      res.status(201).json({ token, userId: id, tenantId, role: 'viewer' });\n    } catch {\n      res.status(409).json({ error: 'Email already registered' });\n    }\n  });\n\n  // POST /auth/login\n  router.post('/auth/login', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const { email, password } = req.body as { email?: string; password?: string };\n    if (!email || !password) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'email and password required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const user = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?').get(email) as\n      | { id: string; tenant_id: string; role: string; password_hash: string }\n      | undefined;\n    if (!user || user.password_hash !== hashPassword(password)) {\n      res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const token = signToken({ userId: user.id, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role });\n    res.json({ token, userId: user.id, tenantId: user.tenant_id, role: user.role });\n  });\n\n  // GET /me\n  router.get('/me', authMiddleware, (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const user = db\n      .prepare('SELECT id, email, tenant_id, role, created_at FROM users WHERE id = ?')\n      .get(auth.userId);\n    if (!user) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json(user);\n  });\n\n  // PATCH /users/:id/role  (admin only, same tenant)\n  router.patch('/users/:id/role', authMiddleware, (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    if (auth.role !== 'admin') {\n      res.status(403).json({ error: 'Admin only' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const { role } = req.body as { role?: string };\n    const validRoles = ['admin', 'editor', 'viewer'];\n    if (!role || !validRoles.includes(role)) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'role must be admin, editor, or viewer' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const result = db\n      .prepare('UPDATE users SET role = ? WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .run(role, req.params.id, auth.tenantId);\n    if (result.changes === 0) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found in your tenant' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json({ updated: true });\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Events Router (Ingestion)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/events.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/events.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\ninterface EventInput {\n  name?: string;\n  properties?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  timestamp?: string;\n}\n\nexport function createEventsRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // All event routes require auth\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  // POST /events  – single event\n  router.post('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { name, properties = {}, timestamp = new Date().toISOString() } =\n      req.body as EventInput;\n    if (!name) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'name is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = uuidv4();\n    db.prepare(\n      'INSERT INTO events (id, tenant_id, name, properties, timestamp) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n    ).run(id, auth.tenantId, name, JSON.stringify(properties), timestamp);\n    res.status(201).json({ id });\n  });\n\n  // POST /events/batch\n  router.post('/batch', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { events } = req.body as { events?: EventInput[] };\n    if (!Array.isArray(events) || events.length === 0) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'events array required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const insert = db.prepare(\n      'INSERT INTO events (id, tenant_id, name, properties, timestamp) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n    );\n    const insertMany = db.transaction((evts: EventInput[]) => {\n      const ids: string[] = [];\n      for (const evt of evts) {\n        if (!evt.name) continue;\n        const id = uuidv4();\n        insert.run(\n          id,\n          auth.tenantId,\n          evt.name,\n          JSON.stringify(evt.properties ?? {}),\n          evt.timestamp ?? new Date().toISOString()\n        );\n        ids.push(id);\n      }\n      return ids;\n    });\n    const ids = insertMany(events);\n    res.status(201).json({ inserted: ids.length, ids });\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Query Engine Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/query.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/query.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\ninterface QueryBody {\n  type: 'count' | 'timeseries' | 'breakdown';\n  eventName?: string;\n  filters?: Record<string, string>;\n  // timeseries options\n  startDate?: string;\n  endDate?: string;\n  interval?: 'day' | 'hour' | 'week';\n  // breakdown options\n  breakdownProperty?: string;\n}\n\nexport function createQueryRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  router.post('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const body = req.body as QueryBody;\n\n    if (!body.type) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'type is required (count|timeseries|breakdown)' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      switch (body.type) {\n        case 'count': {\n          let sql = 'SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ?';\n          const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n          if (body.eventName) {\n            sql += ' AND name = ?';\n            params.push(body.eventName);\n          }\n          const row = db.prepare(sql).get(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]])) as {\n            count: number;\n          };\n          res.json({ count: row.count });\n          break;\n        }\n\n        case 'timeseries': {\n          const intervalFormat =\n            body.interval === 'hour'\n              ? '%Y-%m-%dT%H:00'\n              : body.interval === 'week'\n              ? '%Y-W%W'\n              : '%Y-%m-%d';\n          let sql = `\n            SELECT strftime('${intervalFormat}', timestamp) as bucket, COUNT(*) as count\n            FROM events\n            WHERE tenant_id = ?\n          `;\n          const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n          if (body.eventName) {\n            sql += ' AND name = ?';\n            params.push(body.eventName);\n          }\n          if (body.startDate) {\n            sql += ' AND timestamp >= ?';\n            params.push(body.startDate);\n          }\n          if (body.endDate) {\n            sql += ' AND timestamp <= ?';\n            params.push(body.endDate);\n          }\n          sql += ` GROUP BY bucket ORDER BY bucket`;\n          const rows = db.prepare(sql).all(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]));\n          res.json({ series: rows });\n          break;\n        }\n\n        case 'breakdown': {\n          if (!body.breakdownProperty) {\n            res.status(400).json({ error: 'breakdownProperty required for breakdown query' });\n            return;\n          }\n          const prop = body.breakdownProperty;\n          let sql = `\n            SELECT json_extract(properties, '$.\"${prop}\"') as value, COUNT(*) as count\n            FROM events\n            WHERE tenant_id = ?\n          `;\n          const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n          if (body.eventName) {\n            sql += ' AND name = ?';\n            params.push(body.eventName);\n          }\n          sql += ' GROUP BY value ORDER BY count DESC';\n          const rows = db.prepare(sql).all(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]]));\n          res.json({ breakdown: rows });\n          break;\n        }\n\n        default:\n          res.status(400).json({ error: 'Unknown query type' });\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      res.status(500).json({ error: String(err) });\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Dashboards Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/dashboards.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/dashboards.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\ninterface DashboardRow {\n  id: string;\n  tenant_id: string;\n  name: string;\n  owner_id: string;\n  config: string;\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport function createDashboardsRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  // GET /dashboards\n  router.get('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const rows = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE tenant_id = ? ORDER BY created_at DESC')\n      .all(auth.tenantId) as DashboardRow[];\n    res.json(\n      rows.map((r) => ({ ...r, config: JSON.parse(r.config) }))\n    );\n  });\n\n  // POST /dashboards\n  router.post('/', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { name, config = {} } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: object };\n    if (!name) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'name is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = uuidv4();\n    const now = new Date().toISOString();\n    db.prepare(\n      'INSERT INTO dashboards (id, tenant_id, name, owner_id, config, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)'\n    ).run(id, auth.tenantId, name, auth.userId, JSON.stringify(config), now, now);\n    res.status(201).json({ id, name, tenantId: auth.tenantId });\n  });\n\n  // GET /dashboards/:id\n  router.get('/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const row = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .get(req.params.id, auth.tenantId) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n    if (!row) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json({ ...row, config: JSON.parse(row.config) });\n  });\n\n  // PATCH /dashboards/:id\n  router.patch('/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const { name, config } = req.body as { name?: string; config?: object };\n    const existing = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .get(req.params.id, auth.tenantId) as DashboardRow | undefined;\n    if (!existing) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const now = new Date().toISOString();\n    const newName = name ?? existing.name;\n    const newConfig = config !== undefined ? JSON.stringify(config) : existing.config;\n    db.prepare(\n      'UPDATE dashboards SET name = ?, config = ?, updated_at = ? WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?'\n    ).run(newName, newConfig, now, req.params.id, auth.tenantId);\n    res.json({ updated: true });\n  });\n\n  // DELETE /dashboards/:id\n  router.delete('/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const result = db\n      .prepare('DELETE FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .run(req.params.id, auth.tenantId);\n    if (result.changes === 0) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json({ deleted: true });\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Export Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/export.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 2, Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/routes/export.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { authMiddleware, JwtPayload } from '../auth.js';\n\nfunction rowsToCsv(rows: Record<string, unknown>[]): string {\n  if (rows.length === 0) return '';\n  const headers = Object.keys(rows[0]);\n  const lines = [\n    headers.join(','),\n    ...rows.map((r) =>\n      headers\n        .map((h) => {\n          const val = r[h];\n          const str = val === null || val === undefined ? '' : String(val);\n          // Escape quotes and wrap in quotes if contains comma, quote, or newline\n          if (str.includes(',') || str.includes('\"') || str.includes('\\n')) {\n            return `\"${str.replace(/\"/g, '\"\"')}\"`;\n          }\n          return str;\n        })\n        .join(',')\n    ),\n  ];\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function createExportRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.use(authMiddleware);\n\n  // GET /export/events?format=json|csv&eventName=...\n  router.get('/events', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n    const eventName = req.query.eventName as string | undefined;\n\n    let sql = 'SELECT * FROM events WHERE tenant_id = ?';\n    const params: unknown[] = [auth.tenantId];\n    if (eventName) {\n      sql += ' AND name = ?';\n      params.push(eventName);\n    }\n    sql += ' ORDER BY timestamp DESC';\n\n    const rows = db.prepare(sql).all(...(params as [unknown, ...unknown[]])) as Record<\n      string,\n      unknown\n    >[];\n\n    if (format === 'csv') {\n      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n      res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', 'attachment; filename=\"events.csv\"');\n      res.send(rowsToCsv(rows));\n    } else {\n      res.json(rows);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // GET /export/dashboards/:id?format=json|csv\n  router.get('/dashboards/:id', (req: Request, res: Response): void => {\n    const auth = req.auth as JwtPayload;\n    const format = (req.query.format as string) ?? 'json';\n    const dashboard = db\n      .prepare('SELECT * FROM dashboards WHERE id = ? AND tenant_id = ?')\n      .get(req.params.id, auth.tenantId) as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;\n\n    if (!dashboard) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Dashboard not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (format === 'csv') {\n      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/csv');\n      res.setHeader('Content-Disposition', `attachment; filename=\"dashboard-${req.params.id}.csv\"`);\n      res.send(rowsToCsv([dashboard]));\n    } else {\n      res.json({ ...dashboard, config: JSON.parse(dashboard.config as string) });\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build check**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1 | head -30\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: App Entry Point\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/app.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Tasks 1–7\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/app.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { openDb } from './db.js';\nimport { createUsersRouter } from './routes/users.js';\nimport { createEventsRouter } from './routes/events.js';\nimport { createQueryRouter } from './routes/query.js';\nimport { createDashboardsRouter } from './routes/dashboards.js';\nimport { createExportRouter } from './routes/export.js';\n\nexport function createApp(db?: Database.Database): express.Application {\n  const database = db ?? openDb();\n  const app = express();\n\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  // Mount routers\n  app.use('/', createUsersRouter(database));\n  app.use('/events', createEventsRouter(database));\n  app.use('/query', createQueryRouter(database));\n  app.use('/dashboards', createDashboardsRouter(database));\n  app.use('/export', createExportRouter(database));\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Full build**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run build 2>&1\n```\n\nExpected: no errors.\n\n**Step 3: Lint**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run lint 2>&1\n```\n\nExpected: no errors.\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tests/app.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 8\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/tests/app.test.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../app.js';\nimport { openDb } from '../db.js';\n\nfunction makeApp() {\n  const db = openDb(); // fresh in-memory DB each time\n  return createApp(db);\n}\n\ndescribe('User Management', () => {\n  it('registers a new user and returns a token', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const res = await request(app).post('/auth/register').send({\n      email: 'alice@example.com',\n      password: 'secret',\n      tenantId: 'acme',\n    });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(res.body.role).toBe('viewer');\n  });\n\n  it('rejects duplicate email', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'a@b.com', password: 'x', tenantId: 't1' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'a@b.com', password: 'y', tenantId: 't1' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(409);\n  });\n\n  it('logs in with correct credentials', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'b@c.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 't2' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/login')\n      .send({ email: 'b@c.com', password: 'pw' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.token).toBeTruthy();\n  });\n\n  it('rejects wrong password', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'c@d.com', password: 'correct', tenantId: 't3' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/login')\n      .send({ email: 'c@d.com', password: 'wrong' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n\n  it('returns profile for /me', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const reg = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'd@e.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 't4' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get('/me')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${reg.body.token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.email).toBe('d@e.com');\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for /me without token', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const res = await request(app).get('/me');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Data Ingestion', () => {\n  it('ingests a single event', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'e@f.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenant1' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/events')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeTruthy();\n  });\n\n  it('ingests a batch of events', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'f@g.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenant2' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({\n        events: [\n          { name: 'click', properties: { button: 'signup' } },\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/about' } },\n        ],\n      });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.inserted).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('returns 401 for unauthenticated event ingestion', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const res = await request(app).post('/events').send({ name: 'test' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Query Engine', () => {\n  async function setupWithEvents() {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token, tenantId } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'q@r.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'queryTenant' });\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({\n        events: [\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' }, timestamp: '2024-01-01T10:00:00Z' },\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/about' }, timestamp: '2024-01-01T11:00:00Z' },\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' }, timestamp: '2024-01-02T10:00:00Z' },\n          { name: 'click', properties: { button: 'cta' }, timestamp: '2024-01-02T12:00:00Z' },\n        ],\n      });\n    return { app, token, tenantId };\n  }\n\n  it('counts all events', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'count' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(4);\n  });\n\n  it('counts events by name', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'count', eventName: 'page_view' });\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(3);\n  });\n\n  it('returns timeseries bucketed by day', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'timeseries', eventName: 'page_view', interval: 'day' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.series.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('returns breakdown by property', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setupWithEvents();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'breakdown', eventName: 'page_view', breakdownProperty: 'url' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.breakdown[0].value).toBe('/home');\n    expect(res.body.breakdown[0].count).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('enforces tenant isolation in queries', async () => {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: t1 } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'ta@a.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenantA' });\n    const { body: t2 } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'tb@b.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'tenantB' });\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/events')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t1.token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'secret_event' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/query')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${t2.token}`)\n      .send({ type: 'count' });\n    expect(res.body.count).toBe(0);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Dashboard CRUD', () => {\n  async function setup() {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'dash@test.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'dashTenant' });\n    return { app, token };\n  }\n\n  it('creates and retrieves a dashboard', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const create = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'My Dashboard', config: { widgets: [] } });\n    expect(create.status).toBe(201);\n    const id = create.body.id;\n    const get = await request(app)\n      .get(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(get.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(get.body.name).toBe('My Dashboard');\n  });\n\n  it('updates a dashboard', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const { body: { id } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'Old Name' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .patch(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'New Name' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.updated).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  it('deletes a dashboard', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const { body: { id } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'To Delete' });\n    const del = await request(app)\n      .delete(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(del.status).toBe(200);\n    const get = await request(app)\n      .get(`/dashboards/${id}`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(get.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Data Export', () => {\n  async function setup() {\n    const app = makeApp();\n    const { body: { token } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/auth/register')\n      .send({ email: 'exp@test.com', password: 'pw', tenantId: 'expTenant' });\n    await request(app)\n      .post('/events/batch')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({\n        events: [\n          { name: 'page_view', properties: { url: '/home' } },\n          { name: 'click', properties: { button: 'cta' } },\n        ],\n      });\n    return { app, token };\n  }\n\n  it('exports events as JSON', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get('/export/events?format=json')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body)).toBe(true);\n    expect(res.body.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('exports events as CSV', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get('/export/events?format=csv')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.headers['content-type']).toMatch(/text\\/csv/);\n    expect(res.text).toContain('page_view');\n  });\n\n  it('exports dashboard as JSON', async () => {\n    const { app, token } = await setup();\n    const { body: { id } } = await request(app)\n      .post('/dashboards')\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)\n      .send({ name: 'Export Me' });\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .get(`/export/dashboards/${id}?format=json`)\n      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.name).toBe('Export Me');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm test 2>&1\n```\n\nExpected: all tests pass.\n\n**Step 3: Full lint + build**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm run lint && npm run build 2>&1\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Commit\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 9\n\n**Step 1: Commit all source**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: implement multi-tenant analytics dashboard API\"\n```\n\n**Step 2: Review diff**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && git diff HEAD~1 --stat\n```\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
